{"title_page": "Leonel Moreira", "text_new": "{{short description|Costa Rican footballer}}\n{{Spanish name|Moreira|Ledezma}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2012}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name = Leonel Moreira\n|image = Leonel Moreira.jpg\n|caption = Moreira with [[Club Sport Herediano|Herediano]] in 2016\n|fullname = Leonel Gerardo Moreira Ledezma\n|birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1990|4|4}}\n|birth_place = [[Heredia, Costa Rica]]\n|height = 1.79 m<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_SQUADLISTS.PDF|title=2018 FIFA World Cup: List of players|publisher=FIFA|format=PDF|page=6|date=24 June 2018|access-date=24 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619164139/https://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_SQUADLISTS.PDF|archive-date=19 June 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n|currentclub = [[Liga Deportiva Alajuelense|Alajuelense]]\n|clubnumber = \n|years1 = 2009\u20132019 | clubs1 = [[Club Sport Herediano|Herediano]] | caps1 = 276 | goals1 = 0\n|years2 = 2019      | clubs2 = [[C.F. Pachuca|Pachuca]] | caps2 = 0 | goals2 = 0\n|years3 = 2019      | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Club Bol\u00edvar|Bol\u00edvar]] (loan) | caps3 = 23 | goals3 = 0\n|years4 = 2020\u2013     | clubs4 = [[Liga Deportiva Alajuelense|Alajuelense]] | caps4 = 7 | goals4 = 0\n|nationalyears1= 2011\u2013\n|nationalteam1= [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]]\n|nationalcaps1= 14 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n|pcupdate = 1 March 2020\n|ntupdate = 30 June 2019\n}}\n'''Leonel Gerardo Moreira Ledezma''' (born 4 April 1990) is a Costa Rican [[Association football|football]] player, currently playing for [[Liga Deportiva Alajuelense]] and for the [[Costa Rica national football team]]. Moreira plays as a goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/people/costa-rica/54197/leonel-moreira/national|title=Profile|date=|work=Goal.com|accessdate=9 June 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nMoreira came through the Herediano youth system<ref>[http://wfnode01.nacion.com/2011-06-27/Deportes/Tricolor-carecera-de-experiencia-en-el-arco.aspx Tricolor carecer\u00e1 de experiencia en el arco 3 J\u00f3venes opciones] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006154407/http://wfnode01.nacion.com/2011-06-27/Deportes/Tricolor-carecera-de-experiencia-en-el-arco.aspx |date=6 October 2014 }} \u2013 Naci\u00f3n {{in lang|es}}</ref> and has only played for the ''Florenses''.\n\n==International career==\nMoreira was in Costa Rica's [[2009 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] squad,<ref name=FIFA>{{FIFA player|270136}}</ref> where Costa Rica finished 4th after losing to [[Hungary national under-21 football team|Hungary]] in the 3rd place match.\n\nHe made his senior debut for [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] in a July [[2011 Copa Am\u00e9rica]] match against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]]<ref>[http://www.nacion.com/deportes/futbol-costa-rica/Moreira-solo-cumplio-termino-figura_0_1205279523.html Debutantes con buena actuaci\u00f3n Moreira no solo cumpli\u00f3, sino que termin\u00f3 como la figura] \u2013 Naci\u00f3n {{in lang|es}}</ref> and has, as of May 2014, earned a total of 5 caps, scoring no goals. He was a non-playing squad member at the [[2011 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2011]] and [[2013 CONCACAF Gold Cup]]s.\n\nIn May 2018 he was named in Costa Rica's [[Costa Rica national football team|23 man squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>https://www.goal.com/en/amp/news/costa-rica-names-23-man-world-cup-squad-featuring-keylor/1bw2iz8pkma5614bzushqyyo7g</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===International===\n:''Statistics accurate as of match played 22 June 2018.''<ref>{{NFT player|43894|Leonel Moreira|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!colspan=3|[[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2011||3||0\n|-\n|2012||0||0\n|-\n|2013||0||0